    <name>Linux Show Player</name>
    <summary>Cue player designed for stage productions</summary>
    <developer_name>Francesco Ceruti</developer_name>
    <update_contact>ceppofrancy@gmail.com</update_contact>
    <description>
        <p>
            Linux Show Player, LiSP for short, is a free cue player, mainly intended for sound-playback in stage productions,
            the goal is to provide a complete playback software for musical plays, theater shows and similar.
        </p>
        <p>Some highlights:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>List layout</li>
            <li>Cart layout</li>
            <li>Concurrent cues playback</li>
            <li>Pre/Post wait</li>
            <li>Undo/Redo changes</li>
            <li>Realtime sound effects</li>
            <li>Peak and ReplayGain normalization</li>
            <li>MIDI and OSC support</li>
        </ul>
    </description>
